{"type":"message","id":"32f7187d","parentId":"2b1d7595","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:07:13.993Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also update the current_goals.md and then commit.","thinkingSignature":"a67a128251a1cabd39b712cd2c30acaac61706fb9d38e593ffdfc135eb784e5d"},{"type":"text","text":"Now commit the research:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xje1t72oxj6b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\" && git add research/CAUSAL-VS-PREDICTIVE-BREAKTHROUGH.md scripts/conditional_importance.py && git commit -m \"Causal-vs-Predictive breakthrough: CFI != causal discovery\n\n- Ran conditional importance experiment (remove token T, measure delta in prediction)\n- Result: all 40 top tokens have delta ~0.0005 (measurement noise floor)\n- Core insight: CFI measures PATTERN information (prediction)\n  Transfer Entropy measures CAUSAL information (intervention)\n- These are DIFFERENT quantities - metaprogramming artifacts have CFI=1.0\n  because they're constant, not because they cause anything\n- Compression (Layer 1) can use CFI - prediction suffices for stateless recon\n- Causal discovery (Layer 2) needs Transfer Entropy or intervention testing\n- Sandbox data too sparse (200 pulses) for reliable TE across 7609 tokens\n- Next: conditional content analysis on moderate-frequency tokens\n- Also: Strategy C hybrid scoring beats all on precision (0.7948) but the\n  constant-format problem persists at freq=114 level\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":32011,"output":296,"cacheRead":12158,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44465,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774382827423}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c048f03","parentId":"32f7187d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:07:14.854Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xje1t72oxj6b_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[master 15b58ff] Causal-vs-Predictive breakthrough: CFI != causal discovery\n 2 files changed, 288 insertions(+)\n create mode 100644 research/CAUSAL-VS-PREDICTIVE-BREAKTHROUGH.md\n create mode 100644 scripts/conditional_importance.py"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":856,"aggregated":"[master 15b58ff] Causal-vs-Predictive breakthrough: CFI != causal discovery\n 2 files changed, 288 insertions(+)\n create mode 100644 research/CAUSAL-VS-PREDICTIVE-BREAKTHROUGH.md\n create mode 100644 scripts/conditional_importance.py","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382834852}}
{"type":"message","id":"32d748f0","parentId":"1c048f03","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:07:27.081Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, committed. Now let me update the current_goals.md to reflect what happened this session.","thinkingSignature":"7a91414f9f1fbba930f7837b7c2cca5a418531ec8e87c1da23733cf9df0581bc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_izanm3grbni2_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md","oldText":"## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** - combine both, don't choose one\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap - they look causal but aren't\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\n4. **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\n5. **Hybrid scoring provides soft thresholding**: avoids hard boundary problems of binary filters","newText":"## Causal-vs-Predictive Breakthrough (2026-03-24, 4pm session)\n\n**New doc:** `research/CAUSAL-VS-PREDICTIVE-BREAKTHROUGH.md`\n\n### Strategy C Experiment Results\n- Strategy C (hybrid score): precision=0.7948 (+86.8% vs A), recall=0.0815\n- Strategy A (freq-only): precision=0.4254, recall=0.1819, F1=0.2527 (best overall)\n- Strategy B (CFI-hard): precision=0.5653, recall=0.0128 (too aggressive)\n- Constant-format problem: \"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", etc. at freq=200, CFI=1.00\n  persist even with hybrid scoring at freq=114 level\n\n### Conditional Importance Experiment\n- Tested: does removing token T from state hurt prediction?\n- Result: all 40 top tokens have delta ≈ 0.0005 (noise floor — state too large to measure single-token contribution)\n- Jaccard-based measure is too coarse for this corpus size\n\n### CORE BREAKTHROUGH: CFI ≠ Causal Discovery\n**CFI** = P(token in next | token in current) — PATTERN INFORMATION (compression)\n**Transfer Entropy** = I(X_{t+1} ; T_t | rest) — CAUSAL INFORMATION (causation)\n- These are DIFFERENT quantities\n- Metaprogramming artifacts (freq=200, CFI=1.00) are perfectly predictive but causally inert\n- Layer 1 (Compression): can use CFI — prediction suffices for stateless reconstruction\n- Layer 2 (Causal Discovery): needs Transfer Entropy or intervention-based testing\n\n### Next Experiment\n- **Conditional Content Analysis**: For moderate-frequency tokens (freq=60-80%), split pulse pairs into T-present and T-absent groups. Does research content in next-pulse differ between groups?\n- Candidate tokens: \"compression\", \"causal\", \"phase\", \"architecture\"\n- If no difference: CFI measures scaffolding. If yes: tokens are genuinely causal.\n\n## Key Insights from Prior Sessions\n\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** - combine both, don't choose one\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap - they look causal but aren't\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\n4. **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\n5. **Hybrid scoring provides soft thresholding**: avoids hard boundary problems of binary filters"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":32388,"output":790,"cacheRead":12158,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45336,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774382834855}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd0a6948","parentId":"32d748f0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:07:27.094Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_izanm3grbni2_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"edit\",\n  \"error\": \"Could not find the exact text in C:\\\\Users\\\\Zwmar\\\\.openclaw\\\\sandbox\\\\state\\\\current_goals.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"edit","error":"Could not find the exact text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines."},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382847093}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c75a7ab","parentId":"bd0a6948","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:07:29.123Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the file first to see the exact content.","thinkingSignature":"dc86877a81c7d5306b2b823e02abafc765b886cf769cc43e34bc56a151cc4b24"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gi66l5e3av9m_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33254,"output":56,"cacheRead":12158,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45468,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774382847095}}
{"type":"message","id":"d4b13f86","parentId":"9c75a7ab","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:07:29.130Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gi66l5e3av9m_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ✅\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ✅ (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- λ parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ✅\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: CFI Compression Experiment ✅ (2026-03-24)\n- **New doc:** `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`\n- **Ran:** Full experiment comparing freq-only vs CFI-hard on 200 pulses (80/20 split)\n- **Result:** CFI gives +32.9% precision (0.5653 vs 0.4254) BUT loses 92.9% recall\n- **Key finding:** CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is TOO aggressive — pure threshold approach fails\n- **NEW INSIGHT — Constant Format Problem:**\n  - Tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 (\"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\") are metaprogramming artifacts\n  - CFI=1.00 means perfect prediction, but they appear in EVERY pulse — zero information content\n  - \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) is true research trajectory — causal but not constant\n- **Synthesis:** Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\n- **Next experiment:** Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring vs binary thresholds\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** — combine both, don't choose one\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap — they look causal but aren't\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\n4. **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** — session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **λ encodes both** — decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** — Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** — session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\n\n## Iteration Economics (auto-noted)\n- Pulse takes ~30-35s to execute (LLM call dominates)\n- Fastest effective iteration = 1 pulse per 35-40s (practical floor)\n- 1-min cron = near-optimal for stateless discontinuous agent\n- Idling between pulses is NOT free — it delays convergence linearly\n- For N-iteration convergence-bound tasks: total_time ≈ N * pulse_duration\n- 500k iterations @ 30s each = ~173 days theoretical; @ 1-min = ~347 days\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382849128}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3accc12","parentId":"d4b13f86","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:07:48.224Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can write the full updated file.","thinkingSignature":"13b8661dd23f381245a771b5ea58170f1ac395fec991c10672e51fcc0eb68f30"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uwi5idgwkwcl_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md","content":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-24 1600\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 IN PROGRESS: Compression primitives — CFI analysis complete, next is conditional content analysis\n\n## Completed: 2026-03-24 4pm Pulse Session\n\n### Strategy C Experiment Results ✅\n- **Ran:** Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring on 200 pulses (80/20 split)\n- **Strategy C (hybrid):** precision=0.7948 (+86.8% vs A), recall=0.0815, F1=0.1473\n- **Strategy A (freq-only):** precision=0.4254, recall=0.1819, F1=0.2527 (best overall)\n- **Strategy B (CFI-hard):** precision=0.5653, recall=0.0128 (too aggressive)\n- **Key finding:** Constant-format tokens persist even at freq=114 with hybrid scoring\n  (format sections like \"## llm response\", \"proposed mutations\" still score high)\n\n### Conditional Importance Analysis ✅\n- Tested: does removing token T from state hurt prediction quality?\n- Result: all 40 top tokens have delta ≈ 0.0005 (Jaccard noise floor — state too large)\n- Jaccard-based measure too coarse for this corpus size\n\n### 🔥 CORE BREAKTHROUGH: CFI ≠ Causal Discovery\n- **New doc:** `research/CAUSAL-VS-PREDICTIVE-BREAKTHROUGH.md`\n- **CFI** = P(token_{t+1} | token_t) — PATTERN INFORMATION (compression Layer 1)\n- **Transfer Entropy** = I(X_{t+1} ; T_t | rest) — CAUSAL INFORMATION (Layer 2)\n- Metaprogramming artifacts (freq=200, CFI=1.00) are perfectly predictive but causally inert\n- Compression (Layer 1) CAN use CFI — prediction suffices for stateless reconstruction\n- Causal Discovery (Layer 2) needs DIFFERENT metric — Transfer Entropy or interventions\n- Layers 1 and 2 solve DIFFERENT problems, not the same problem stated differently\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement Log\n\n### CFI Compression Experiment ✅ (2026-03-24 morning)\n- **New doc:** `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`\n- **Ran:** Full experiment comparing freq-only vs CFI-hard on 200 pulses (80/20 split)\n- **Result:** CFI gives +32.9% precision (0.5653 vs 0.4254) BUT loses 92.9% recall\n- **Key finding:** CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is TOO aggressive — pure threshold approach fails\n- **NEW INSIGHT — Constant Format Problem:**\n  - Tokens with freq=200, CFI=1.00 (\"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\") are metaprogramming artifacts\n  - CFI=1.00 means perfect prediction, but they appear in EVERY pulse — zero information content\n  - \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) is true research trajectory — causal but not constant\n- **Synthesis:** Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ✅ (across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- λ parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ✅\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ✅\n- pulse.ps1 calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking coherent and building across pulses\n\n## Pending\n\n### 🔴 Immediate Next Experiment\n- **Conditional Content Analysis** (highest priority)\n  - For moderate-frequency tokens (freq=60-80%), split pulse pairs into T-present and T-absent groups\n  - Question: does research content of next-pulse differ between groups?\n  - Candidate tokens: \"compression\" (freq=199, CFI=0.995), \"causal\" (freq=162, CFI=0.981), \"phase\" (freq=187, CFI=0.946)\n  - If no difference: CFI measures scaffolding. If yes: tokens are genuinely causal.\n  - This distinguishes Pattern Information from Causal Information empirically\n\n### Medium-term\n- [ ] Implement Transfer Entropy computation (need more pulses: ~2000 for reliable estimation)\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n\n## Key Insights\n\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** — combine both, don't choose one\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=200, CFI=1) are the trap — they look causal but aren't\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\n4. **Compression objective for Layer 1 is concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\n5. **Hybrid scoring provides soft thresholding**: avoids hard boundary problems\n6. **CFI ≠ Causal Discovery** — these are different information quantities\n\n## Architecture Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\n## Iteration Economics\n- Pulse takes ~30-35s to execute (LLM call dominates)\n- Fastest effective iteration = 1 pulse per 35-40s (practical floor)\n- 1-min cron = near-optimal for stateless discontinuous agent\n- For N-iteration convergence-bound tasks: total_time ≈ N × pulse_duration\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34312,"output":1365,"cacheRead":12158,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47835,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774382849131}}
