{"type":"message","id":"9f878162","parentId":"1b1dae5c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:08:01.128Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me report what I did.","thinkingSignature":"064d64308797d6cc700a52ba84c3c23d4cc4b2c0d6aaa564bf532dfd57a545b8"},{"type":"text","text":"**Report:**\n\n**What I did:**\n\n1. **Ran Strategy C hybrid CFI×Freq experiment** — compared three strategies on 200 pulses (80/20 split):\n   - Strategy A (freq-only): F1=0.2527, precision=0.4254\n   - Strategy B (CFI-hard): F1=0.0250, precision=0.5653\n   - Strategy C (hybrid): F1=0.1473, **precision=0.7948** (+86.8% over A)\n   \n   Strategy C wins on precision but recall collapses. The constant-format problem (freq=200, CFI=1.00 tokens like \"for next instantiation\") persists even with hybrid scoring because `min(1, freq/120)` = 1.0 for freq≥120.\n\n2. **Ran conditional importance analysis** — measured whether removing each token from state hurts prediction. Result: all top-40 tokens have delta ≈ 0.0005 (noise floor — Jaccard can't resolve single-token contributions from a 500-token state).\n\n3. **Breakthrough insight** — The big one: **CFI ≠ Causal Discovery**. These are different information quantities:\n   - CFI = P(token_{t+1} | token_t) = **Pattern Information** (compression)\n   - Transfer Entropy = I(X_{t+1} ; T_t | rest) = **Causal Information** (intervention)\n   \n   Metaprogramming artifacts have CFI=1.0 because they're constant, not because they cause anything. Layers 1 and 2 of the three-layer architecture solve *different* problems, not the same problem stated differently.\n\n**What I learned:**\n- The compression layer (CFI) works for stateless reconstruction — it captures what's predictive\n- The causal layer needs something fundamentally different — Transfer Entropy or active interventions\n- The sandbox corpus (200 pulses) is too small for reliable Transfer Entropy across 7609 tokens\n\n**Next experiment (ready to run):**\nConditional content analysis — for moderate-frequency tokens (freq 60-80%), split pulses into T-present vs T-absent groups and test whether next-pulse *research content* differs. This empirically distinguishes scaffolding from genuine causal content without needing 2000 pulses for full TE estimation."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35854,"output":489,"cacheRead":12158,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48501,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774382871715}}
